# Project Setup Guidelines

## Node Version
- Use Node.js version 22 or higher as specified in package.json
- Ensure .nvmrc is present and matches the engine requirement
- Use pnpm as the package manager (as evidenced by pnpm-lock.yaml)

## Environment Variables
Always validate environment variables using Zod schemas:

```typescript
const envSchema = z.object({
  REQUIRED_VAR: z.string().min(1),
  OPTIONAL_VAR: z.string().optional(),
  PORT: z.string().transform(Number).default("3000"),
});

const env = envSchema.safeParse(process.env);
if (!env.success) {
  console.error("Invalid environment variables:", env.error.format());
  process.exit(1);
}
```

## TypeScript Configuration
- Use strict mode in tsconfig.json
- Enable ESM modules (type: "module" in package.json)
- Maintain explicit return types on exported functions
- Use path aliases for clean imports when possible

## Scripts
Standard npm scripts should include:
- `build`: Compile TypeScript
- `start`: Run production server
- `dev`: Development mode with watch
- `test`: Run test suite
- Add descriptive prefixes for specialized scripts (e.g., `test:mcp`, `test:rest`)
